          <msContents>
            <summary>Selection from the larger purāṇic work (adhyāya 31) dedicated to the Hindu deity Viṣṇu. Selection deals with the problem of sin (pāpa), its causes, as well as the means to remove it for the purpose of being liberated from the snares of the cycle of life and death (samsāra). The worship of Nārāyaṇa (a form of Viṣṇu) is presented as one means of liberation. Additional note at the end of manuscript in second hand, written in Marathi, indicating the former owner of the text (f. 18r)</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit and Marathi</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Bṛhannāradīyapurāṇa</title>
